      "message": "[error] Line 1590: This race guard still depends on `info.removed` being unique at millisecond resolution. If `acceptConversationRequest()` observes the tombstone and a newer local removal updates `info.removed` within the same millisecond before `cloneConversationFrom()`/`handlePendingConversation()`, the equality check can pass and the clone-success path will clear the newer tombstone, resurrecting a conversation the user removed. Use a monotonic generation/token updated under the conversation lock on every local removal, store that token with the pending re-invite, and compare the token instead of the timestamp.\n```suggestion\n// Pseudocode: compare a monotonic removal generation, not info.removed.\nif (expectedRemovalGeneration \u0026\u0026 *expectedRemovalGeneration !\u003d conv-\u003eremovalGeneration) {\n    JAMI_WARNING(\"[Account {}] [Conversation {}] Removed again while accepting a re-invitation, aborting the clone\",\n                 accountId_,\n                 request.conversationId);\n    return;\n}\nconv-\u003ereinvitePending \u003d conv-\u003eremovalGeneration;\n```",
