      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 2216: The race guard assumes a newer local removal will always have a different millisecond timestamp. That is not guaranteed: accepting a re-invite and removing the conversation again within the same millisecond can leave `conv-\u003einfo.removed` unchanged, making `handlePendingConversation()` clear the tombstone and resurrect a conversation the user just removed. Use an explicit generation/nonce for the removal state, or compare against an in-memory monotonic marker updated on every removal instead of relying on wall-clock millisecond uniqueness.\n\n```suggestion\n// Store and compare a monotonic removal generation instead of relying on\n// millisecond timestamp uniqueness.\nstd::optional\u003cuint64_t\u003e removalGeneration;\n```",
